iam H. Gass, and Jamaica Kincaid, and relative newcomers such as Lorrie Moore, Kirstin Valdez Quade, Phil Klay, Viet Thanh Nguyen, and Edward P. Jones. Why I Like This Story will send readers to the library or bookstore to read or re-read the stories selected. Among the contributors to the book are Julia Alvarez, Andrea Barrett, Richard Bausch, Ann Beattie, Andre Dubus, George Garrett, William H. Gass, Julia Glass, Doris Grumbach, Jane Hamilton, Jill McCorkle, Alice McDermott, Clarence Major, Howard Norman, Annie Proulx, Joan Silber, Elizabeth Spencer, and Mako Yoshikawa. Editor Jackson R. Bryer is Professor Emeritus of English at the University of Maryland.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthors, AmericanxBooks and reading. 0aAuthors, AmericanxReading interests. 0aInfluence (Literary, artistic, etc.). 0aShort stories, AmericanxHistory and criticism. 4aEnglish & American Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican literature.  aAmerican short stories.  acontemporary fiction.  acreative writing.  aelements of fiction.  aessay collection.  aliterary friendship.  ashort story.  awriters as readers.1 aAbbott, Lee K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAckerman, Elliot, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlvarez, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAskew, Rilla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarrett, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBausch, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeattie, Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBetts, Doris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aB